== Tiwuriwin ==
Yara Yuba mnnnaw n idlisn s Tgrikt f umzruy, amzruy amagan, tarakalt, tajṛṛumt, takʷlut d umzgun. Iskr yan usmzazal gr tmrsal tigrikin d tṛumiyin s uzwl Όμοιότητες (Resemblances)<ref>F Jacoby, ''[[Realencyclopädie der Classischen Altertumswissenschaft]]'', 1916, s.v.</ref>. Amanar-nns s [[Tagzirt n aɛṛabbn|Arabya]] idwl adlis akkʷ inzzan ɣ Ṛuma. Ɣar kra n igzzumn imẓẓiyn sg twuri-nns ad aɣ-d-ilkmn.

Mrawt twuriwin n Yuba ad ittyussann, maccan llan ɣar kra n igzzumn zgi-sn:
* ''Roman Archaeology'', sin ildisn<ref name=RollerAppendix>Duane W. Roller, ''The World of Juba II and Kleopatra Selene'' (Routledge, 2003), pp. 61–63. {{ISBN|0-415-30596-9}}.</ref>.
* ''Resemblances'', ɣ kkuẓ idlisn iɣ idrus<ref name=RollerAppendix/>.
* ''On Painting'', ɣ tam idlisn iɣ idrus<ref name=RollerAppendix/>.
* ''Theatrical History'', ɣ sa d mraw n idlisn iɣ idrus<ref name=RollerAppendix/>.
* ''The Wanderings of Hanno'', iẓḍar ad ig asuɣl n umuddu n Ḥanno<ref name=RollerAppendix/>.
* ''On Euphorbion'', a pamphlet<ref name=RollerAppendix/>.
* ''Libyka'', ɣ kraḍ idlisn iɣ idrus.<ref name=RollerAppendix/>.
* ''On Arabia'', wad waḥdu-t ad yara s tutlayt talatint<ref name=Roller165>Duane W. Roller, ''The World of Juba II and Kleopatra Selene'' (Routledge, 2003), p. 165. {{ISBN|0-415-30596-9}}.</ref>.
* ''On Assyria'', ɣ sin idlisn<ref name=RollerAppendix/>.
* ''Epigrams'', ibdr-d zgi-s [[Athinyus]] (Athenaeus) sḍis n izrirn lli fllas nssn<ref name=RollerAppendix/>.

